\title{readecb: Access European Central Bank Data}
\description{
Provides clean, tidy access to statistical data published by the European Central Bank (ECB) via the ECB Data Portal API \url{https://data.ecb.europa.eu}. Covers policy interest rates, euro exchange rates, harmonised consumer price inflation (HICP), euro area yield curves, the euro short-term rate (ESTR), monetary aggregates (M1, M2, M3), and mortgage and lending rates. Each dataset has a dedicated function that abstracts away the underlying SDMX key structure, so users do not need to know series codes. A generic fetcher is also provided for direct access to any of the ECB's 100-plus dataflows. Data is downloaded on first use and cached locally for subsequent calls. Unlike the existing 'ecb' package, which provides a low-level SDMX interface requiring knowledge of series keys, 'readecb' offers named convenience functions, uses a lightweight dependency stack ('httr2' and 'cli' only), returns CSV rather than XML, and caches results locally.
